<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-31-0817 </DOCNO><TEXT>Hydrogenated amorphous silicon thin film transistor (a-Si: H) is expectedhaving wide applications such as photoelectric elements represented bythe solar cell and field effect elements represented by thin film transistor(TFT) owing to properties of which other semiconductors do not have.The experimental and theoretical investigations were carried out on thedrain current drift phenonena after the trial manufacture of a-Si H TFT.It was clarified as the results that the drain current drift phenimenahad long time constanta, so that these phenomena indicated very complexbehaviors. It was further clarified that the drift phenomena were casuedby the capture of electrons in channel by the interfacial level distributedspacially, by comparing measurenents of drain current drift taking sufficientlycare of the initial state with theoretical calculations. (12 figs, 2tabs, 23 refs)</TEXT></DOC>